  "title": "PROJECT ENGINEER",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities:<br /></p><p>• Undertaking civil engineering design, review and project management for a wide range of projects, including land development, road infrastructure, high-density retail, and other civil infrastructure Providing assistance to different staff or engineering teams.</p><p>• Collaborating with other engineers and workers to design, develop, test, and improve products and engineering processes.</p><p>• Prepare technical reports, cost estimates, and project specifications</p><p>• Monitor construction progress and ensure compliance with safety standards</p><p>• Manage and coordinate the work of contractors and other personnel involved in civil engineering projects</p><p>• Research and evaluate new technologies and materials for civil engineering projects<br /></p><p>Requirements:<br /></p><p>• Degree in Engineering or Building</p><p>• Good knowledge and experience in building-related works such as civil engineering, structural, architectural, building repair, carpentry, partition, renovation, plumbing works, etc</p><p>• Experience in the construction of building projects, including M&E facilities installation and maintenance regime is preferred</p><p>• Possesses excellent communication and interpersonal skills</p><p>• Must have initiative and drive to resolve site issues to achieve project success</p><p>• Proficient in MS Work & Excel and drafting of letter</p><p>Kindly include the following on your CV/Resume:</p><p>• Last drawn Salary</p><p>• Expected Salary</p><p>• Availability and Notice Period</p>",
